    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>marinade</strong></p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in<strong> cold water</strong> to prevent them from burning</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide your <strong>mince</strong> into 2 per person and press onto each <strong>skewer</strong> to form a long sausage shape \u2013 these are your<strong> mince skewers</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> mince skewers</strong> to a baking tray (use<strong> tin foil </strong>to avoid mess!)</p><p>Press the mince to flatten it slightly and drizzle over the <strong>marinade </strong>(reserve the bowl!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15 min, turning once, or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 these are your <strong>Kambing-style mince skewers</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>peanut butter</strong> and a small splash of <strong>boiled water </strong>in the reserved bowl and mix until well combined</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong>,<strong> sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up until well combined \u2013 this is your <strong>satay sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and separate the <strong>leaves</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/satay-kambing-style-lamb-skewers-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong> and <strong>sliced tomato </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>and top with the <strong>Kambing-style mince skewers</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> satay sauce </strong>and<strong> cauliflower rice </strong>to the side and garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
